there have been numerous problems/bad features with the hot-spot mode=20
on sun's linux vm, the reason for this is that hot-spotting is=20
optimizing your code by doing very weird stuff with your code :-)

anyway i'm glad -classic works well for you. the bad performance is a=20
known problem with the linux-kernel java threading system. When it=20
comes to threads windows jvms outperforms linux jvms because of kernel=20=

internal things i don't even try to understand...

i have used the 1.3.1 linux jvm from ibm with great stability, how does=20=

the ibm jvm perform against the sun jvm when it comes to thread=20
performance?

there is also a 1.3 jvm from a group called "blackdown" that is free=20
and optimized for linux. there was some talking in the news about it=20
being very good at threading... you could try it..  (=20
http://www.blackdown.org/ )

mvh karl =F8ie



