X-Spam-Rating: daedalus.apache.org 1.6.2 0/1000/N

i had such problems with norwegian characters and it resolved into=20
making sure the querystring has the same encoding as the index has.

since this is again a java.lang.String encoding question i had these=20
problems with querystrings coming from java Servlets and CLI. For both=20=

the quickfix was to re-encode the query in UTF-8/16:

String querystring =3D argv[0]; ' String querystring =3D=20
httprequest.getParameter("query");
querystring =3D new String(querystring.getBytes("UTF-8"));
...

this fixed my norwegian/samii problems...


mvh karl =F8ie

