Hello,
> I use lucene 1.2 and I index a text document wich size is near 500 =
ko.
> (I use Field.UnStored method)
> It seems that only the beginning of this document is indexing !
> If I search a term that is at the end of this document, I=20
> don't find it (but
> If find term at the beginning).
> So, I split my document in 2 parts and index them, and now it=20
> works fine.
>=20
> Is there a limit size for indexing a document ?
You are right. There is a limit for the number of terms for each field, =
but
you can
change it. Look at org.apache.lucene.index.IndexWriter for =
maxFieldLength.
The default limit is set to 10000 terms. A 500k document contains more =
terms
depending on stopwords and number of white spaces. That why the end of =
your
document
was ignored.
Regards,

