 > -------------------------------
 > Linux and Sun JDK 1.2.x - 1.3.x:
 > -------------------------------
 >
 > Virtual machine crashes can be experienced when using certain=20
combinations of
 > kernel / glibc under Linux with Sun Hotspot 1.2 to 1.3. The crashes=20=

were
 > reported to occur mostly on startup. Sun JDK 1.4 does not exhibit the=20=

problems,
 > and neither does IBM JDK for Linux.
 >
 > The problems can be fixed by reducing the default stack size. At bash=20=

shell,
 > do "ulimit -s 2048"; use "limit stacksize 2048" for tcsh.
 >
 > GLIBC 2.2 / Linux 2.4 users should also define an environment=20
variable:
 > export LD_ASSUME_KERNEL=3D2.2.5





