On Tuesday 15 October 2002 08:50, you wrote:
> I want to write a function countIndexEntries(key) to find out how many
> entries are there in the index database for a key. I read the faq entry
> about counting number of hits, but somehow it doesnt work as expected,
> please help:
>
> I create entries with
> =09=09indexDocument.add(Field.Keyword(FULLTEXT_KEY_FIELD,key));
> =09=09indexDocument.add(Field.Text(FULLTEXT_CONTENTS_FIELD,reader));
> =09=09indexwriter.addDocument(indexDocument);
>
> I try to count the number of entries for a key with
> =09=09Query query =3D QueryParser.parse(key, FULLTEXT_KEY_FIELD, analyz=
er);
> =09=09count =3D searcher.search(query).length();
>
> to find out if something is not yet indexed (count=3D0), already indexe=
d
> (count=3D1), or index is inconsistent (count=3D2). But count is always =
=3D 0 :-(

This might depend on your analyzer.
For key fields, I prefer to use a lower level API on IndexReader:
construct a Term from the field name and the key value and use the=20
IndexReader method that returns an iterator over the docs containing the=20
term, termdocs() iirc. Beware of correct case for the key value.
In case you have mutliple key values to check, sorting them before going =
to=20
the  IndexReader helps performance
For pure boolean work, the IndexReader is quite useful.

> What is wrong or how to acchieve my goal with a different approach? Hel=
p is
> appreciated.

It should work I think. You might try and print the output of the analyze=
r,=20
ie the actually indexed text, when constructing the document.

Have fun,
Ype

